                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240218-171-off935 t18240218-171-crimeloc938"></join>. On the 12th of February, the prisoner came to the shop, other shopmen were present. I was carrying some stuffs to the counter, heard one fall off the pile, turned round, and saw him crossing the street with a piece under his arm - it had stood under the door. I pursued, he threw it down, and the watchman took him without my losing sight of him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I throw myself on the mercy of the Court.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 17.</p>

